<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.clantaveren.com" target="top">Clan Ta Veren</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aericspellbinder>Aeric Spellbinder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 3:03:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4668.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No</span><hr size=1> would be nice to know what this effect really does. i heard many different rumors already:<br>
rumor 1) increases the chance to stun a target by certain amount % (Bash II=20%,III=30%, etc.)<br>
rumor 2) increases the hate from your taunt weapon by a certain % so the aggro from an EB weapon with Furious Bash II would be 700+20% = 840<br>
rumor 3) it turns your bash damage into aggro (plus the added %), so if you bash for 50dmg with Furious Bash II, you get 50+20% = 60 aggro.<br>
rumor 4) combined effects of rumor 2 + rumor 3<br>
<br>
sadly i couldn't get an official answer to describe the effect. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9564" target="top">Aeric Spellbinder - 64 Warlord of the North</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.thestoic.com" target="top">Stoic - Povar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=y0shimitzu>y0shimitzu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 10:31:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4668.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   lucy says</span><hr size=1> well according to lucy.  it is what raaj said..   you input the percent number as the lvl of bash...  ie bash 2 is 20% bash 7 is 70%.  what the actual effect does... I have not clue but I would really like to know. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=y0shimitzu>y0shimitzu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 11:00:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4668.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   my conclusion</span><hr size=1> ok after doing some research on this.  it seems that furious bash is a focus effect, and it is a timed dot lasting 1 tick at lvl 1 and 3.3 minutes at lvl 65. (so it last about 1 tick longer every 2 lvls )  and a focus effect goes off when ever you use the trigger.  which seems to be doing a bash. <br>
<br>
so what that says use the sheild and bash, switch it out.  you just put a dot on that mob that increases your spell/bash hate by X%.  so with that in mind I would assume that it means your hate proc weapons ( spells casted by you ) would have that hate increase by X%.  or any weapon proc for that matter.  so say your frosty give off about 100 points of hate on proc.   ( just a random number ) if you had a fierce bash 2 sheild and had the dot in.  you would get 120 points of hate.  <br>
<br>
THAT IS FREAKING AWESOME!  just my 2 cent and my take on what it is all about. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aruza>aruza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 11:06:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4668.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my conclusion</span><hr size=1> We just need some beefy 1handers or let us equip shields with 2handers /shrug...<br>
Ruza <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=togr>Togr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 11:13:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4668.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Bash...</span><hr size=1> If this is a dot then it wouldn't be character specific, thus anyone landing a spell or bash has the hate increased by 20%.  IE, this procs and the chain nuking wizzie bites the dust... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=varaho1>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1197<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 11:56:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4668.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Zek Crusted Buckler? Warrior focus effect??</span><hr size=1> Fungi has a HoT spell built into it too you know~ <br>
